quark.config.title: Quark Configuration
quark.config.qdisabled: (If you disable the q button, you can access this menu from the Mods list)
quark.config.needrestart: (Some settings you changed will require you to restart your game)
quark.config.importinfo0: You can import a list of disabled features from the Quark Website
quark.config.importinfo1: using this menu. In the website, click the checkmark on any feature
quark.config.importinfo2: you wish to disable. When you're done, click the Copy button.
quark.config.importinfo3: You can import it by pasting (press Ctrl+V) to the text field.
quark.config.importinfo3m: You can import it by pasting (press Cmd+V) to the text field.
quark.config.disabledcount: %d Features Disabled. Please Restart your game:
quark.config.disabledcount1: 1 Feature Disabled. Please Restart your game:
quark.config.cantimport: Can't Import a Config if a world is loaded
quark.config.firstloadinfo0: Welcome to Quark! Quark has a lot of features, so check the Quark Website
quark.config.firstloadinfo1: for a quick primer. Every feature can be turned off, so feel free to
quark.config.firstloadinfo2: hit the Configure Quark button to disable features you don't like.
quark.config.firstloadinfo3: In the Configuration menu you can use the Import Config button to
quark.config.firstloadinfo4: import a list of disabled features from the quark website.
quark.config.firstloadinfo6: If you are going to play on a Vanilla server, or a modded server that
quark.config.firstloadinfo7: doesn't have Quark installed. You NEED to disable every module except
quark.config.firstloadinfo8: for Client, or you will find incompatibilities and/or crashes. If you're
quark.config.firstloadinfo9: playing on a server with Quark, don't disable anything outside Client.
